\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Ye who listen with credulity to the whispers of fancy, and pursue with eagerness the phantoms of hope; who expect that age will perform the promises of youth, and that the deficiencies of the present day will be supplied by the morrow; attend to the history of Rasselas prince of Abissinia.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Rasselas was the fourth son of the mighty emperour, in whose dominions the Father of waters begins his course; whose bounty powers down the streams of plenty, and scatters over half the world the harvests of Egypt.}
